cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.GR

Reasoning: 
1. cs.RO (Robotics): The paper describes the development of a surgical system using the da Vinci research kit (dVRK) which involves the use of robotics for autonomous searching of tumors. 
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The system uses augmented reality to dynamically display the tumor location, which involves computer vision techniques. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia): The system involves the use of multimedia technologies such as augmented reality to display the tumor location. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The system uses active level set estimation to find the location and shape of tumors, which involves the use of AI techniques. 
5. cs.GR (Graphics): The system involves the dynamic overlay of estimated stiffness maps onto the registered preoperative model of the organ, which involves graphics techniques.
